the lab to deal with a possible outbreak.

158
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:16,825
目前, 只要机会允许
我一定会派个人来接你
Now, if an opportunity arises,
I will send someone to come get you,

159
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:19,369
不过在此之前, 我们只能通过无线电联系
but in the meantime, radio contact will have to do.

160
00:10:20,495 --> 00:10:21,538
好吧
All right.

161
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:24,541
那就...让我们保持联系
Just...keep us in the loop.

162
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,626
会的
Will do.

163
00:10:29,504 --> 00:10:34,050
这些破碎敞开容器中的任何一个都有可能
释放出病毒, 杀死了Johnson和Wagner
Any number of these smashed and open containers could
have released the virus that killed Johnson and Wagner.

164
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:36,553
那这种东西怎么可能活了这么些年?
And how would something like that
survive for all these years?

165
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,805
病毒可以长时间保持休眠状态.
Viruses can remain dormant for long periods.

166
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:41,349
希望可以在数据库中找到答案.
I'm hoping the answer will be found in the database.

167
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:44,477
- 好吧, 我想我们应该...
- 是的, 是的, 是的.
- Okay, I think that we have to...
- Yes, yes, yes.

168
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,563
看不出跟古人的其他系统有什么网络连接
Doesn't appear to be networked in
with the rest of the Ancient systems.

169
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:49,607
事实上, 正如你看到的, 这只保存了
In fact, if you look, it only contains information

170
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,901
在这个房间里所进行的实验的信息
about the experiments that took place in this room.

171
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:54,654
Weir, 我是McKay.
Weir, it's McKay.

172
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,031
说吧, Rodney.
Go ahead, Rodney.

173
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,699
- Beckett在哪?
- 在路上
- Where's Beckett?
- On his way.

174
00:10:57,741 --> 00:10:59,993
让整个医疗队都穿上防护服需要一些时间
It takes some time to load
a whole medical team into suits.

175
00:11:00,118 --> 00:11:03,455
好吧, 看起来我们偶然发现了什么
我发现了...一个小麻烦
Well, we seem to have stumbled across
something that I find... a little troubling.

176
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:05,874
这不是我想听到的
That's not what I wanted to hear.

177
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:08,626
我想我们找到了一个古人的病毒实验室
I think we may have found an ancient viral lab.

178
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,378
Wagner和Johnson一定是在这里被感染的
Wagner and Johnson must have been exposed here.

179
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:12,255
目前, 查看所有这些数据需要数周的时间
Now, it'd take weeks to sift through all this data,

180
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:13,923
而且, 我们也不知道古人到底是
and there's no way of knowing whether the Ancients

181
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,426
仅仅只是研究这些病毒
或者是在积极地制造它们...
were just studying the viruses
or actively creating them...

182
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:18,845
不管是那种情况, 风暴已经把这里破坏得一塌糊涂
Either way, the storm has done
quite a number on this place,

183
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:19,929
并且我们已经...
and I've got...

184
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,438
它在你上面!
It's all over you!

185
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:32,025
他们在你上面!
他们在你上面!
They're all over you!
They're all over you!

186
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:33,902
让她躺下
Get her off.

187
00:11:53,505 --> 00:11:54,798
告诉Beckett快点赶来
Tell Beckett to pick up the pace.

188
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:57,008
我们刚刚失去另外一个队员
I've just lost another member of our team.

189
00:11:57,676 --> 00:11:58,885
Peterson在哪?
Where's Peterson?

190
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:00,512
什么?
What?

191
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:01,596
Peterson.
Peterson.

192
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:12,440
是的, 好了, 我想我们找到他了
Yes, okay, I think we have him.

193
00:12:12,482 --> 00:12:13,817
他正在找路回来
He's trying to make his way back.

194
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:15,235
应该没事的
It should be okay.

195
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,988
Grodin正在锁住走廊中所有的门
然后切断整个区域的电源
Grodin is locking all the doors in the hallway
and killing power to the entire section.

196
00:12:19,364 --> 00:12:21,449
你需要派人去阻止他
You need to send someone to stop him.

197
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,867
都在控制之中, Rodney...
It's under control, Rodney...

198
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:24,953
不, Elizabeth, 不在控制之中
No, Elizabeth, it's not under control.

199
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:27,747
他所知道的古人的科技不比我少
He knows almost as much about
Ancient technology as I do.

200
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:31,001
你所做的一切至多也只能让他慢一点
At the very most,
what you're doing will just slow him down.

201
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,936
那条走廊通向哪里?
Where does that hallway lead?

202
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:52,022
一直到这里
Straight here.

203
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:01,072
Peterson, 我是Elizabeth Weir.
Peterson, this is Elizabeth Weir.

204
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,449
能听到我说话么?
Can you hear me?

205
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:06,161
我无法想象这整个经历是多么的令人恐惧
I can't imagine how frightening
this whole ordeal must be,

206
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:10,874
不过Beckett博士已经找到了你们其他队员
并且开始医治他们
but Dr. Beckett has reached the rest
of your team and begun to treat them.

207
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,836
现在, 你现在最应该做的就是返回去
Now, I think the best thing
for you to do is to head back.

208
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:19,632
如果Beckett证明你完全健康
我们保证你可以尽快回到城市中来
If Beckett gives you a clean bill of health, we'll make
sure you get back to the city as soon as possible.

209
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:26,848
你确信他能够听到么?
Are you sure he can hear me?

210
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:28,266
肯定
Positive.

211
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:31,227
你能让通过这些门更困难一些么?
Can you do anything to make it harder
to get through those doors?

212
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:33,271
我可以试试
I can try.

213
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,789
好了, 你看起来非常好
Well, you seem perfectly fine.

214
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:52,916
Dumais在她突然不好之前, 看起来也非常好
Well, Dumais seemed fine right up
to the point where she wasn't.

215
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:55,794
我已经让他们在走廊上搭了一小块地方
I've had them set up
a small field station down the corridor.

216
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,212
我们已经开始尸体解剖了
We've already started the autopsies.

217
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:58,213
有什么看法?
Any ideas?

218
00:13:58,254 --> 00:13:59,964
从现在来看,
你一切都好, 所以我不会...
From what we can tell,
you're all in good shape, so I wouldn't...

219
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:02,217
不要再告诉我我一切都好了, Carson.
stop trying to convince me I'm fine, Carson.

220
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,510
我想我们更加了解
I think we all know better.

221
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:05,095
- 我只是想...
- 我们搞完了么?
- I was just trying to...
- Are we done here?

222
00:14:05,929 --> 00:14:06,763
是的
224
Yes.

223
00:14:07,597 --> 00:14:09,140
我要看看我可以从数据库中找到什么
I'm going to see what I can get from the database.

224
00:14:09,182 --> 00:14:10,809
尸体解剖有什么结果, 马上告诉我
Let me know what the autopsy shows up.

225
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:11,810
好的
All right.

226
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:14,896
噢, 告诉你那些病理学家
从他们的头部开始
Oh, and tell your pathologists
to start with their heads.

227
00:14:46,261 --> 00:14:48,138
必须有人做些什么
Someone has to do something.

228
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,806
我们正在做
We are doing something.

229
00:14:49,973 --> 00:14:51,975
Grodin正在想办法限制门的控制...
Grodin's working on a plan to limit door controls...

230
00:14:52,017 --> 00:14:54,310
这还不够好
必须有人去阻止他
That's not good enough.
Someone has to go out there and stop him.

231
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:55,603
我和Teyla已经准备好了
Teyla and I are ready.

232
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:56,479
少校, 我们已经...
Major, we've been...

233
00:14:56,521 --> 00:15:00,692
Peterson的想法很明显是错误的
他将会让城市中的所有人处于危险之中
Peterson obviously isn't thinking straight,
and he's endangering the entire population of the city.

234
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:02,944
我们现在仍然不知道我们所对付的病毒的习性
We don't yet know the nature
of the virus we're dealing with.

235
00:15:02,986 --> 00:15:05,113
这仍然只是一个医学状况
This is still a medical situation.

236
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,115
我们没必要浪费时间了
我要出去了
We don't have time for this. I'm heading out.

237
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,491
Grodin, 封住体育馆.
Grodin, seal the gym.

238
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:15,915
这到底是怎么回事?
What the hell is this?

239
00:15:15,957 --> 00:15:18,835
你自己说的
你是最高军事指挥官
You said so yourself.
You are the ranking military officer.

240
00:15:18,877 --> 00:15:20,587
我不能让你有机会感染病毒
I can't chance you getting infected.

241
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:23,089
我不能让你有机会感染病毒. Bates?
I can't chance you getting infected. Bates?

242
00:15:23,173 --> 00:15:23,965
是的, 长官
Yes, sir.

243
00:15:24,007 --> 00:15:25,050
打开体育馆
Unlock the gym.

244
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:27,260
遵命, 长官
Yes, sir.

245
00:15:27,302 --> 00:15:28,636
站住, Bates.
Stand down, Bates.

246
00:15:28,678 --> 00:15:30,597
这里不归你做主, 少校.
You are not in command here, Major.

247
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,557
好吧, 我们少数服从多数
Well, we'll agree to disagree.

248
00:15:32,682 --> 00:15:34,351
Bates, 把门打开
Bates, open the door.

249
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:37,562
不要
Don't.

250
00:15:37,604 --> 00:15:39,064
Elizabeth, 他正朝你那边过来
Elizabeth, he's heading right for you.

251
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:40,273
所以我们一定要制止他
So we'll stop him.

252
00:15:40,315 --> 00:15:41,775
我们会劝阻他, 我们会堵住他的路...
We'll talk him down, we'll block his way...

253
00:15:41,816 --> 00:15:47,072
Bates中士, 我现在命令你立刻打开
体育馆到医学实验室之间所有的门
Sergeant Bates, I am ordering you to open up
the doors between the gym and the med lab right now.

254
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:56,706
我们准备出去
We're heading out.

255
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,636
对不起, 夫人
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

256
00:16:11,763 --> 00:16:13,682
现在这都不要紧, 是么?
Doesn't really matter now, does it?

257
00:16:24,526 --> 00:16:25,694
Beckett博士?
Dr. Beckett?

258
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:28,822
我已经有了最开始两位遇难者的初步解剖结果
I have the preliminary autopsy results
on the first two victims, Sir.

259
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:30,740
有什么值得关注的?
Anything of interest?

260
00:16:30,782 --> 00:16:33,368
他们都死于大脑动脉瘤破裂
They both died of a ruptured saccular brain aneurysm,

261
00:16:33,535 --> 00:16:35,912
这真是太不寻常了
which, in and of itself, isn't all that remarkable.

262
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:38,581
我的意思是, 两个站在一起的人
I mean, sure, the chances of two people
standing next to each other

263
00:16:38,707 --> 00:16:41,042
同时死于这种原因在统计学上是不可能的
and dying of it is statistically improbable, yes,

264
00:16:41,167 --> 00:16:44,546
不过这不是我们所希望的最终原因,
因为我知道你说过...
but it's not the smoking gun we were hoping for,
because I know you said...

265
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:46,381
直接说真正原因, Biro博士
Get to the good part, Dr. Biro.

266
00:16:46,423 --> 00:16:47,465
对不起, 先生
Sorry, Sir.

267
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:50,885
真正引起我们关注的是
这两起动脉瘤的破裂
What's truly interesting
is that both ruptures happened

268
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:54,389
正巧都发生在相同的区域
刚好在视觉皮层
in exactly the same place,
right above the visual cortex.

269
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:56,516
那么第三个呢? Dumais?
And the third one? Dumais?

270
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:59,019
刚好轮到她了, 先生
Just getting to her now, sir.

271
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,270
我会告诉你的
I'll let you know.

272
00:17:00,562 --> 00:17:01,855
她是说, "大脑动脉瘤," 对么?
She did say, "brain aneurysm," right?

273
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:02,939
是的
That's right.

274
00:17:02,981 --> 00:17:05,275
这是我今天听到的最好的消息了
让我给你看些东西
That's the best news I've heard all day.
Let me show you something.

275
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:15,285
你本不应该在Bates中士面前破坏Weir博士的威信的
You should not have undermined Dr. Weir's
authority in front of sergeant Bates.

276
00:17:15,410 --> 00:17:20,707
有时候, Elizabeth先作出了一个决定,
然后就困在那里面了    这就是问题
Sometimes, Elizabeth makes a decision
early on and gets locked into it. That's a problem.

277
00:17:20,915 --> 00:17:25,462
她并不是唯一遭受这种苦恼的人
She is not the only one who suffers
from that affliction.

278
00:17:28,465 --> 00:17:30,258
Weir博士, 我是Sheppard.
Dr. Weir, this is Sheppard.

279
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:32,385
我和Teyla已经准备好出去了
Teyla and I are ready to head out.

280
00:17:32,552 --> 00:17:34,429
Peterson的位置在哪儿?
What's Peterson's location?

281
00:17:41,353 --> 00:17:43,355
Elizabeth
Elizabeth.

282
00:17:44,481 --> 00:17:46,983
他在E-19区, 第三层
He's in section E-19, level three.

283
00:17:55,325 --> 00:17:56,368
我们走
Let's head out.

284
00:18:36,199 --> 00:18:38,284
我没有读完整个条目
因为它实在是太长了
I haven't read the entire entry
because it's incredibly long,

285
00:18:38,410 --> 00:18:39,744
不过这看起来像我们这些家伙
but this looks like our guy.

286
00:18:39,786 --> 00:18:42,747
六小时休眠
重复出现的幻觉, 然后, 在这之后,
Six-hour hibernation,
recurring visions, and, best of all,

287
00:18:42,831 --> 00:18:46,167
我们最后...
大脑出血或者动脉瘤
so I've left it to last...
brain hemorrhage or aneurysms.

288
00:18:46,418 --> 00:18:48,294
这听起来非常熟悉
That definitely sounds familiar.

289
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:50,171
也许这里有讲如何...
Maybe there's something in here about how to...

290
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:55,760
不!
No!

291
00:19:03,685 --> 00:19:04,686
抱歉
Sorry.

292
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:08,023
Rodney.
Rodney.

293
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:15,864
我刚才看见什么东西了
I've been seeing things.

294
00:19:17,157 --> 00:19:18,825
从什么时候开始的?
Since when?

295
00:19:20,118 --> 00:19:21,369
大约一个小时了
About an hour.

296
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:24,539
开始你会认为这只是你的眼睛在欺骗你, 不过最终...
First you think it's just your eyes
playing tricks on you, but eventually...

297
00:19:24,581 --> 00:19:25,957
它们变得更糟
they get worse.

298
00:19:27,459 --> 00:19:28,668
你也是?
You too?

299
00:19:30,128 --> 00:19:31,463
他们直冲你过来
They come right at you.

300
00:19:34,341 --> 00:19:36,426
看起来像鬼魂
It's like a ghost.

301
00:19:36,801 --> 00:19:38,386
我已经去检查过了调查计划
I've been going over the survey schedule.

302
00:19:38,428 --> 00:19:40,513
Johnson和Wagner从他们的位置出发
Johnson and Wagner started off on their own,

303
00:19:41,181 --> 00:19:43,725
不过接着一小时后将穿过Dumais所经过的路线
but then crossed paths with Dumais an hour later.

304
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,605
Dumais差不多刚好在Johnson和Wagner之后一小时死去
Dumais died almost exactly
an hour after Johnson and Wagner.

305
00:19:49,606 --> 00:19:51,107
他们接下来碰到的是谁?
Who did they meet up with next?

306
00:19:51,149 --> 00:19:53,777
我现在最关心的是Dumais接下来碰到的是谁
My greater concern is who Dumais met up with next.

307
00:19:53,818 --> 00:19:54,652
Dumais?
Dumais?

308
00:19:54,986 --> 00:19:56,446
她碰到的是谁?
Who did she run into?

309
00:20:05,955 --> 00:20:06,790
我
Me.

310
00:20:07,999 --> 00:20:09,501
她碰到了Hays...
She ran into Hays...

311
00:20:10,085 --> 00:20:11,127
和我
and me.

312
00:20:13,505 --> 00:20:14,756
我们是下一波
We're next.

313
00:20:26,810 --> 00:20:28,937
Peterson博士, 是你么?
Dr. Peterson, I presume?

314
00:20:29,813 --> 00:20:31,106
我不会回到那去的
I'm not going back there.

315
00:20:31,272 --> 00:20:32,732
你别无选择
You don't have much of a choice.

316
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:36,611
放松...
Easy...

317
00:20:37,987 --> 00:20:41,241
我回到那去, 我就会被感染. 这是谋杀
I go back there, I get infected. That's murder.

318
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:43,368
一旦我们确定你没有受到感染
Once we ensure that you are not infected,

319
00:20:43,410 --> 00:20:45,286
你会被允许返回城市
you will be allowed back into the city.

320
00:20:45,412 --> 00:20:48,540
在那之前, 你对其他人来说都是一个威胁
Until then, you are a threat
to the rest of the population.

321
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:51,751
你不会朝自己人开枪的
You won't shoot a member of your own team.

322
00:20:51,793 --> 00:20:54,796
Peterson, 你没被允许回到城市
Peterson, you will not be allowed
to go back to the city.

323
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:56,589
